57	## Architecture
58	
59	**Pipeline pattern**: `Pipeline` (in `pipeline.py`) orchestrates stages, each independently runnable via the Typer CLI (`cli.py`, exposed as the `worldcup-playoff` entry point `worldcup_playoff.cli:app`):
60	
61	1. **Clean** — `DataLoader` reads raw CSVs → `DataCleaner` merges `matches.csv` with `match_details.csv` on `MATCH_ID`, filters by date, drops draws, fixes zero percentages, adds the binary `HOME_WIN` target → produces `dataset/train_data.csv`
62	2. **Train** — `ClassifierFactory` creates sklearn classifiers → `ClassifierTrainer` fits (temporal split, `shuffle=False`) → `ModelEvaluator` reports metrics → models saved to `output/models/*.joblib`
63	3. **Fit** — `DistributionFitter` fits scipy distributions to each team's per-feature data (using the `fitter` library) → saved to `output/distributions.json`
64	4. **Simulate** — `FeatureSampler` draws synthetic stats from the fitted distributions → `GamePredictor` predicts each single-match tie → `TournamentSimulator` runs N full brackets via Monte Carlo → `ResultPlotter` renders output
65	
66	### Package layout
67	
68	```
69	worldcup_playoff/
70	├── __main__.py         # Enables `python -m worldcup_playoff`
71	├── cli.py              # Typer commands — all user-facing entry points (worldcup_playoff.cli:app)
72	├── config.py           # Pydantic models (AppConfig, BracketConfig, Matchup) loaded from TOML
73	├── pipeline.py         # Orchestrator — wires stages together, only class that touches all subpackages
74	├── types.py            # Classifier Protocol (sklearn interface contract)
75	├── data/
76	│   ├── client.py       # FootballClient — rate-limited football-data.org v4 client with
77	│   │                   #   circuit-breaker retry + session reset; X-Auth-Token from env
78	│   ├── builders.py     # CSV builders (TeamsBuilder, MatchesBuilder, RankingBuilder,
79	│   │                   #   PlayersBuilder, MatchDetailsBuilder) — each fetches from football-data.org
80	│   ├── bracket_builder.py  # Generates a Round-of-32 bracket TOML from qualified teams
81	│   ├── loader.py       # Reads local CSVs into DataFrames with column + dtype validation
82	│   └── cleaner.py      # Merges matches + details, engineers features, filters dates, adds HOME_WIN
83	├── models/
84	│   ├── classifiers.py  # ClassifierFactory (creates SVM/RF/NB), ClassifierTrainer (fit/save/load)
85	│   └── evaluation.py   # ModelEvaluator — classification report + confusion matrix + ROC curves
86	├── simulation/
87	│   ├── distributions.py # DistributionFitter (fitter→scipy), FeatureSampler, FittedDistribution dataclass
88	│   ├── game.py          # GamePredictor — samples features, runs classifier, returns single-tie winner
89	│   └── tournament.py    # TournamentSimulator — Monte Carlo bracket, BracketSlot tree, RoundResult
90	└── visualization/
91	    └── plots.py         # ResultPlotter — bracket PNG and round-probability charts
92	```
93	
94	### Key design choices
95	
96	- **Single-match ties throughout**: `GamePredictor.predict_tie(home, away)` runs one prediction per tie; `TournamentSimulator._play_tie` resolves a tie with a single call (no `_play_series` loop). `SimulationConfig` has no series-length fields.
97	- **Dependency injection throughout**: `GamePredictor` receives classifier + sampler + distributions; `Pipeline` receives config objects. No global state.
98	- **`Classifier` Protocol** in `types.py` — any object with `fit(X, y)` and `predict(X)` works.
99	- **All config is Pydantic models** loaded from TOML (`config/default.toml` for pipeline params, `config/playoff_*.toml` for bracket matchups).
100	- **`FootballClient`** uses a circuit-breaker pattern (3 consecutive failures → 60 s cooldown), exponential backoff with jitter, periodic session resets, and a 6 s default delay tuned for the free 10 req/min tier. The API key is read from `FOOTBALL_DATA_API_KEY` and sent as `X-Auth-Token`; the client still works unauthenticated.
101	- **Deterministic feature heuristics**: `MatchDetailsBuilder` fills shots/possession/pass-accuracy with fixed formulae (`SHOTS = goals*5+7`, `SHOTS_ON_TARGET = max(goals+2, shots//3)`, `POSSESSION = 50.0`, `PASS_PCT = 75.0`) when the free tier omits them — never random, so output is reproducible. Paid-tier statistics override the heuristics.
102	- **`RoundResult.probabilities`** are per-team advancement probabilities (counts / n_simulations), not normalized across teams — they sum to the number of ties in the round, not 1.0.
103	- **Bracket tree** (`BracketSlot`) is built bottom-up from matchups via `build_bracket_tree`; adjacent winners pair into the next round. Matchup-list length must be a power of two (32-team knockout → 16 first-round matchups).
104	- **Team identification by name**: `matches.csv` stores country names directly in `HOME_TEAM` / `AWAY_TEAM`, so the cleaner needs no numeric-ID-to-name mapping (unlike the NBA original). `DistributionFitter` aggregates per-team observations by combining `*_home` columns from home matches with `*_away` columns from away matches.
105	
106	## Configuration
107	
108	- `config/default.toml` — pipeline parameters (data paths, 10 feature columns, classifier hyperparams, distribution candidates, simulation settings, client rate-limit config)
109	- `config/playoff_2026.toml` — bracket definition (16 Round-of-32 matchups with `home` / `away` / `group`); adjacent matchups feed the next round, list length must be a power of two
110	- Environment: `FOOTBALL_DATA_API_KEY` — optional football-data.org token (sent as `X-Auth-Token`)
111	
