### 4. `worldcup_playoff/simulation/` — Monte Carlo Simulation (3 files)

- **distributions.py** — Statistical distribution fitting per team:
  - `FittedDistribution`: immutable dataclass (name, params tuple)
  - `DistributionFitter`: fits scipy distributions (norm, t, f, chi, cosine, alpha, beta, gamma, dgamma, dweibull, maxwell, pareto, fisk) to 5 base stats per team
    - Aggregates: home observations (HOME_TEAM, *_home cols) + away observations (AWAY_TEAM, *_away cols renamed to *_home)
    - Filters by min_season (default 2018) from DATE column
    - Returns dict[team_name, list[FittedDistribution]] (5 distributions per team)
  - `FeatureSampler`: draws synthetic feature vectors from fitted distributions
    - `assemble()`: concatenates home (5) + away (5) samples → 10-D vector for classifier
    - `sample()`: low-level helper using SCIPY_GENERATORS (scipy.stats distribution samplers)
    - Supports optional random_state for reproducibility
- **game.py** — `GamePredictor`: predicts single knockout tie outcome
  - `predict_tie(home, away) -> str`: samples one feature vector per team, feeds concatenated (home + away) to classifier, returns winning team name
  - Fallback to POOLED_KEY distribution for sparse teams
- **tournament.py** — Monte Carlo bracket simulation:
  - `TournamentSimulator`: runs N independent bracket simulations
  - `RoundResult`: dataclass tracking per-team advancement counts and probabilities per round
  - `BracketSlot`: tree node representing a bracket slot (leaf = first-round tie, internal = multi-team aggregate)
  - `build_bracket_tree()`: constructs bracket tree from matchup list (validates power-of-2 length)
  - `extract_bracket_slots()`: returns dict[round_num, list[slots]] by BFS
  - `simulate()`: runs n_simulations full brackets, accumulates round-by-round advancement counts
  - **Supports ONLY fixed knockout bracket** (no live/group-stage simulation yet)

