### 11. Top-level Modules

- **pipeline.py** — `Pipeline` orchestrator: coordinates all stages (clean → train → fit → simulate)
  - Methods: run_build_teams/matches/match_details, run_clean, run_train, run_fit_distributions, run_simulate
  - Composes: DataLoader, DataCleaner, ClassifierFactory/Trainer, DistributionFitter, FeatureSampler, GamePredictor, TournamentSimulator
- **types.py** — `Classifier` Protocol: minimal sklearn-compatible interface (fit, predict)
- **__init__.py**, **__main__.py** — Package entry points
- **__pycache__/** — Compiled modules

---

### Summary of EXISTING Architecture

The codebase is **production-ready for fixed-bracket World Cup knockout prediction** with:
- Complete data pipeline (API → CSV → cleaned training data)
- Three trained classifiers (SVM, Random Forest, Naive Bayes)
- Statistical distribution fitting per team (scipy-based)
- Monte Carlo bracket simulation (single-match knockout only)
- Comprehensive visualization (bracket + probabilities)
- Robust CLI with 9+ commands
- ~250 test cases covering all layers
- No ELO, Poisson, live group-stage, or advanced feature engineering yet
